assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Osoul Investment Company - K.S.C.P, an asset management company, engages in financing and investment activities in Kuwait, Gulf Co-operation council, other Arabian countries, and the United States. The company operates through three segments: Finance, Investment, and Real Estate. It invests in real estate, industrial, agricultural, and economic sectors; acts as an investment portfolio manager; provides technical, economic, advisory, finance brokerage, finance, and leasing services; purchases, develops, sells, and rents real estate properties; purchases and sells securities and bonds; deals and trades in the foreign exchange market and precious metals market; and owns industrial property rights, patents, commercial and industrial trademarks, commercial designs, and literary and intellectual property rights related to programs and writings. The company also invests in Murabaha, Wakala, and deposit in financial institutions; and offers wealth, fund, client portfolio, and real estate management services. In addition, it conducts studies and specializes in analytical research; and engages in the general trading activities. The company was incorporated in 1998 and is based in Kuwait City, Kuwait.
